#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:87
msgid ""
"The `cat /proc/drbd` command is deprecated in DRBD versions 9.x for getting resource status information. After upgrading DRBD, use the `drbdadm status` command to get "
"resource status information."
msgstr ""
"The `cat /proc/drbd` command is deprecated in DRBD versions 9.x for getting resource status information. After upgrading DRBD, use the `drbdadm status` command to get "
"resource status information."

#. type: Title ===
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pausing the Services"
msgstr "サービスの一時停止"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:94
msgid "Now that you know the resources are in sync, start by upgrading the secondary node.  This can be done manually or according to your cluster manager's documentation."
msgstr ""
"リソースが同期されていることがわかったので、まずはセカンダリーノードのアップグレードを開始してください。これは、手動で行うか、クラスターマネージャーのドキュメントに従って行"
"うことができます。"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:97
msgid "Both processes are covered below. If you are running Pacemaker as your cluster manager do not use the manual method."
msgstr "両方の手順について以下で説明します。クラスタマネージャーとしてPacemakerを使用している場合は、手動方法を使用しないでください。"

#. type: Title ====
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manual Method"
msgstr "手動方法"

#. type: delimited block -
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "node-2# systemctl stop drbd@<resource>.target\n"
msgstr "node-2# systemctl stop drbd@<resource>.target\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:108
msgid ""
"To use the `systemctl stop` command with a DRBD resource target, you would have needed to have enabled the `drbd.service` previously. You can verify this by using the "
"`systemctl is-enabled drbd.service` command."
msgstr ""
"DRBDリソースターゲットを使用して`systemctl stop`コマンドを実行するには、事前に`drbd.service`を有効にしておく必要があります。これを確認するには、`systemctl is-enabled drbd."
"service`コマンドを使用することができます。"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:110 /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:273
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pacemaker"
msgstr "Pacemaker"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:113
msgid "Put the secondary node into standby mode. In this example `node-2` is secondary."
msgstr "セカンダリノードを待機モードにします。この例では、`node-2` が副次ノードです。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "node-2# crm node standby node-2\n"
msgstr "node-2# crm node standby node-2\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:120
msgid "You can watch the status of your cluster using `crm_mon -rf` or watch `cat /proc/drbd` until it shows _Unconfigured_ for your resources."
msgstr "クラスターの状態を確認するには、`crm_mon -rf`を使用するか、リソースが「_Unconfigured_」と表示されるまで`cat /proc/drbd`を見ることができます。"

#. type: Title ===
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upgrading the Packages"
msgstr "パッケージのアップグレード"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:126
msgid "Now update your packages."
msgstr "パッケージの更新"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:128
msgid "RHEL/CentOS:"
msgstr "RHEL/CentOS:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "node-2# dnf -y upgrade\n"
msgstr "node-2# dnf -y upgrade\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:134
msgid "Debian/Ubuntu:"
msgstr "Debian/Ubuntu:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "node-2# apt-get update && apt-get upgrade\n"
msgstr "node-2# apt-get update && apt-get upgrade\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:141
msgid "Once the upgrade is finished you will have the latest DRBD 9.x kernel module and `drbd-utils` installed on your secondary node, `node-2`."
msgstr "アップグレードが完了すると、セカンダリノードである「node-2」に最新のDRBD 9.xカーネルモジュールと「drbd-utils」がインストールされます。"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:143
msgid "But the kernel module is not active yet."
msgstr "ただし、カーネルモジュールはまだアクティブではありません。"

#. type: Title ===
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the New Kernel Module"
msgstr "新しいカーネルモジュールの読み込み"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:149
msgid "By now the DRBD module should not be in use anymore, so unload it by entering the following command:"
msgstr "現時点では、もはやDRBDモジュールを使用していないはずなので、次のコマンドを入力してアンロードしてください："

#. type: delimited block -
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "node-2# rmmod drbd_transport_tcp; rmmod drbd\n"
msgstr "node-2# rmmod drbd_transport_tcp; rmmod drbd\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:156
msgid "If there is a message like `ERROR: Module drbd is in use`, then not all resources have been correctly stopped."
msgstr "もし `ERROR: Module drbd is in use` のようなメッセージが表示される場合、すべてのリソースが正しく停止されていない可能性があります。"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/h-kuroki/work/drbd-doc-ja/proto/v9/base/adoc/drbd-upgrading-8.4-to-9.x.adoc:159
msgid "Retry <<s-upgrading-the-packages-v8-to-v9, upgrading packages>>, or run the command `drbdadm down all` to find out which resources are still active."
